      "review_summary": "The PR adds typed Claude CLI rate-limit classification, a UserDefaults-backed five-minute CLI cooldown gate, stale Claude snapshot preservation for typed CLI rate limits, and focused Swift tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the remaining PR blockers from source inspection: set a Claude CLI cooldown, then run the existing one-shot CLI usage path and it remains `.background`, so the PR blocks before invoking Claude. I did not run live Claude or Keychain probes because repository policy avoids those without explicit request.",
